As of the [[census]] of 2010, there were 119 people in 39 households in the town. The racial makeup of the town was 89% [[White (U.S. Census)|white]], 5% Hispanic or Latino, and 2.5% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]].

The population was 45 percent male and 55 percent female. The population was 38.7 percent under 18 and 20 percent 65 or over.

